By Fabian Ekeruche The Bible Society of Nigeria (BSN) says its 54th National Board Meeting scheduled for April 26 to April 30, in Eket, Akwa Ibom will be declared opened by the  Gov. Udom Emmanuel. The BSN’ Manager, Media and Public Relations, Mr Benjamin Mordi, said this in a statement on Tuesday in Lagos. Mordi said that the Meeting would commence with a Divine Service at All Nations Christian Ministry International, Eket on April 28. He said that the meeting would be hosted by the Southern Zone of the Society, and be presided over by its President and Board Chairman, Rev. Dr. Timothy Banwo. “Among other things, the Board Meeting will discuss past and future activities of the organisation concerning Bible work as well as examine BSN’ accounts for the past one year. “The General-Secretary of the BSN, Dr. Dare Ajiboye, is expected to present his report for the year under review to the Board at the meeting,” he said. Mordi said that the Patron of the BSN, Gen. Dr. Yakubu Gowon, GCFR, national officers, delegates from across the country and some senior members of the management team of the Society were expected to be in attendance. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the Bible Society of Nigeria is a not-for-profit interdenominational Christian organization that translates the Bible into Nigerian Languages, publishes, distributes and raises funds for the Bible work. (NAN) Share this:WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket Share this:WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket WhatsAppFacebookTwitterTelegramMoreLinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket LinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket LinkedInTumblrSkypeRedditPinterestPocket Like this:Like Loading... Like Loading...  	Related Bible Society appoints Sanusi as new CEO-DesignateBible Society of Nigeria (BSN) announces appointment of Pastor Samuel Sanusi as its new General Secretary/ Chief Executive Officer-Designate.November 29, 2020In "R